        <type>auto</type>
        <definition>auto erbsland::cterm::theme::layout::encloseInBrackets</definition>
        <argsstring>(std::span&lt; String &gt; texts, const ThemeAccessor &amp;themeAccessor, Part bracketPart, Part textPart) noexcept -&gt; StringWithMargins</argsstring>
        <name>encloseInBrackets</name>
        <qualifiedname>erbsland::cterm::theme::layout::encloseInBrackets</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>std::span&lt; <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_string" kindref="compound">String</ref> &gt;</type>
          <declname>texts</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1theme_1_1_theme_accessor" kindref="compound">ThemeAccessor</ref> &amp;</type>
          <declname>themeAccessor</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1theme_1_1_part" kindref="compound">Part</ref></type>
          <declname>bracketPart</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1theme_1_1_part" kindref="compound">Part</ref></type>
          <declname>textPart</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Enclose a sequence of text parts in brackets using the specified theme accessors. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This will create a string using this structure: <computeroutput> Elements: LB: left bracket MB: middle bracket (separator) RB: right bracket <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_text" kindref="compound">Text</ref>: one of the text elements Attributes: LM: left margin RM: right margin LP: left padding RP: right padding (padding always rendered as spaces in the given theme char style) <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1theme_1_1_theme" kindref="compound">Theme</ref> style: [B: ...] bracketPart [T: ...] textPart</computeroutput></para>
<para><computeroutput>[B:LM] collapsed with [T:LM] -&gt; returned as left margin [B: LB + LP] [T: LP + <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_text" kindref="compound">Text</ref> + RP] [B: RP + MB + LP] [T: LP + <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_text" kindref="compound">Text</ref> + RP] [B: RP + RB] [B:RM] collapsed with [T:RM] -&gt; returned as right margin </computeroutput> <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>texts</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The text to join with surrounding brackets. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>themeAccessor</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The theme accessor to use for styling (selects element, states and tags). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>bracketPart</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The part to use for the bracket styling. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>textPart</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The part to use for the text styling. If set to <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1theme_1_1_part_1a6369213480b27645a87ad845afa3280d" kindref="member">Part::None</ref>, no text styling is applied. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The joined text with surrounding brackets, styled according to the theme accessor. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
